      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, you should never stop taking sertraline and suddenly start taking St. John's wort without consulting your doctor, as combining them can cause severe serotonin syndrome and undermine your anxiety treatment. Even swapping one medication for another without medical supervision is dangerous because the doses and interactions required for safety must be carefully managed by a specialist. Please contact your healthcare provider immediately to discuss managing the nausea safely rather than making unassisted changes to your medication regimen.",
